  "dateModified": "2026-04-27",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-27",
  "description": "California — both the coastal territory and the imaginative screen — has served as the historical laboratory in which the californicational apparatus iterates. The Misiones, the Gold Rush, industrial agriculture, Hollywood, the Bay Area counterculture, Silicon Valley, and the wellness industry are stages of one apparatus, exporting and recombining formatting techniques on a continuous substrate of indigenous displacement and migrant labor.",
  "name": "California as Laboratory",
